While their customer service here is great, if you plan to come here, you better be prepared to not get the same drink every time.  I was here on Sunday, and the drink I received was completely different from the one I ordered a week prior even though I ordered the same exact thing.   They didn't even bother to put ice in my smoothie when they blended it, I felt like I was drinking pumpkin water.  The orange dream machine my husband ordered also tasted like water.  A real shame too because their staff is friendly and they deliver their drinks in a timely manner.< /text>

<gmap_id>0x808580e171f5f34d:0xb02af125828220e9</gmap_id><user_id>117534549190989038650</user_id>< review>
This little gem is delicious.  We stayed in the hotel around the corner and made this our morning breakfast spot every day.  Everything we tried was excellent.  The (I assume owner/s) were, as one review mentioned, a little lacking on customer smiles, but over time they grow on you and they are always professional.  I was particularly enamored of a marble cherry muffin/cupcake that they offer.  LOADS of cherries and melt in your mouth texture.  So soft and moist.  I don't care where I stay in San Fran next time, I'll go out of my way to get one of those next time I visit.< /review>

<userid>112610871944608220477<//userid><user_name>Noemi Casi<//user_name><time>1607329135616< /time><Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
I love this place because I always find some nice tops and I love how organized each section is (by color). I did have a bad experience the first time that I went. I was carrying some clothes that I was going to put back but then I saw a top that I thought was really pretty. I moved the hangers so I could put the clothes there while I looked through that section when an employee approached me and said "No,no. Are you going to put the clothes back?" I responded that I was and she told me to let her so I did. Awhile later, I was looking for my sister so I could put the new clothes I had found in the cart. That's when I saw that employee hurriedly heading over to her co-worker and they were whispering in a gossipy way in spanish. I speak spanish but couldn't overhear exactly what they said. The second employee looked up and saw me and looked back down. She was talking about me probably because she assumed that I wasn't going to put the clothes back according to color. I didn't complain, I just let it go. I've been there a couple times afterwards and haven't experienced anything but great customer service other than that 5 stars.< /text>

<username>Tracy Houston<//username><time>1562703239168<//time><rating>3</rating>< Review>
After shopping around for about two weeks the closest thing to what I wanted was found at Naders,  but unfortunately once I brought it home myself, the furniture pieces did not align properly. I have 10 years of aircraft mechanic experience so it should be a no-brainer to lock in a couple of hinge pieces. Four visits to the showroom later, and ONLY AFTER I purchased the sofa trundle and matching chaise... WAS I  told that maybe there was some finagling I "may" need to do with it to get it to slide in ?
I don't think I should have to do all that just to get a headrest and some arm sleeves together to keep the armrest locked in the recliner next to each other, so I think the furniture is a little misaligned and hopefully the customer service Mgr Jones, who coinsidentally ...was the 1st person I met on the floor upon my intial visit. ... will help me resolve this,  and I'll have a better review after this is all over.  But right now Im sitting on a half assembled couch and sofa chaise for Memorial Day üòï UPDATE.... I was eventually able to get in touch with the manager there I believe his name was Christian and he had a gentleman come to my home after work and take care of the furniture situation and I am thoroughly pleased now, as they rectified the issue,  and I would recommend them to anyone looking for moderately priced furniture pieces.< /Review>

The management was always quick to do repairs, maintenance, or anything I asked really. The unit itself was very nice and perfect for me at that time in my life. The pool and amenities along with the grasses and garden areas were all kept in tip top shape making the living experience more than just an apartment. When my lease ended with Eaglewood, I moved out.  They tried to charge me for a month's rent for the month _after_ I left.  I explained to them, calmly, that that is not how leases work, and there was no mandatory notice provision in the lease.  I was angrily shouted at.

I moved away, figuring my security deposit a loss.  Then they sent a collections agency after me.  I went to small claims court.  The judge explained to them, somewhat bewildered, that leases end when they say and that you can't punish people with made up charges just because you didn't want them to leave.

These people are scum.  American Property Management had to settle a class action suit over inappropriately withholding security deposits.  They know the law.  They just don't care. <Review>Terrible place to live, go elsewhere.

The management is awful, they are unwilling to help and always choose the cheapest route. The appartments themselves are run down and old, with many appliances broken to a point where cause a danger, for example drier needs to be run more than 3 times to actually dry a small load. The buildings are in terrible condition with many walls pealing, ceilings cracked and some partially falling, ceiling lamps melted and not maintained.

The worst part is the parking. There are a small amount of unreserved parking spaces but they get filled up by early afternoon with tons of "reserved" spaces remain empty even after 2am. The problem being if your 1 per appartment reserved spot is taken, you have nowhere to park. They just say go park outside the complex on the street (which usually is also already filled aswell because it neighbours residential streets).

I could go on about other terrible thing about these appartments and the horrid management, such as much higher prices etc. Do yourself a favor and do not go here. Avoid at all costs.< /Review><Rating>1< /Rating>< user_name>

< review>
My wife and I purchased a 2021 RAV4 from Craig Edwards (the internet sales manager) at the dealership last Friday and the entire experience was exceptional.  As other reviewers have noted, all employees were properly masked, professional, well dressed, knowledgeable and personable.  We "built" our car online and the dealer sent us an offer before we made the trip.  The dealership includes a snack bar so that we could eat while we waited for the financial paperwork, they had a good sized inventory of cars, and they offered us a very generous amount of money for our 2012 Prius which we traded in.

We do not live near the dealership, but we drove the close to two hours to get there because they had what we were looking for.  Craig was a straight shooter, no typical dealer negotiating and nit picking.  We appreciated that and left very happy with the entire transaction.

As for COVID issues, all employees wore masks at all times, there were ample locations for hand sanitizer, and there was at least one employee making the rounds throughout our time there sanitizing surfaces on the showroom floor, on the doors, at the tables, in the restrooms.  It was very reassuring and we felt completely safe while we waited.

We enthusiastically recommend Craig, Joseph, Ilya, Oscar and all of the folks we dealt with during our transaction for various aspects of the sale and would certainly put them at the top of the list as the best place in Southern California to buy a Toyota.<//review>

This oil is only required to be changed at 10,000-mile intervals. The exception to this rule is a vehicle that is being used as a Taxi or Uber and making frequent, short trips at temperatures below 32 F/0 C. This situational driving pattern would require oil changes at 5,000-miles.\n\nToyotaCare no cost Maintenance Plan:\n\n5,000  = Tire rotation & multipoint inspection\n10,000= Oil change, tire rotation & multipoint inspection\n15,000= Tire rotation & multipoint inspection\n20,000= Oil change, tire rotation & multipoint inspection\n25,000= Tire rotation & multipoint inspection\n\nAll ToyotaCare services must be performed before 2 years or 25,999 miles, whichever comes first.\n\nHope this helps\nToyota of Lancaster"}</Response>

My last experience was not that great. I don't think i am coming back to this dealership as I can no longer trust the service dept to perform work on my car.
Prior to stopping in for my 15k mile service appointment, I had marked my rear tires with paint as I wanted to be sure that they would get rotated. So I drop off my car and wait in the refreshment room. An hour and a half later, I get a call informing me the car is ready. My service advisor reviewed all the work done to my car included tire rotation. After signing the work order paper I was escorted to my car. When I inspected the car, I noticed the  tires were never rotated, as the marked tires were still in the rear. Needless to say, I walked back into the office to inform my service advisor about the issue. He said he would find out who worked on my car. A moment later his manager and the tech came out. The first thing the manager asked was "are you sure you marked the rears and not the fronts?" I said I marked the rears and my tires were not rotated despite being shown as completed on the work order. The tech was like do you want me to rotate the tires again?? I'm like dude you never rotated my tires. It made me wonder if the other items on the checklist were actually performed. This is why I do my own maintenance work on my other cars. Think twice before taking your car here as they have some techs that don't do their jobs properly.

In response to the dealership reply below:

Why would they not move the rear tires to the front when the fronts were more worn out?? It's a front wheel drive car!!! Front tires wear out faster than rears so you would want tires with good thread dept in the front. Also  the Dealership  Marked rotation as Completed! If the tires could not be rotated then they should not have stated tire rotation as done.<//review>

<user_name>Dio Javier< /user_name><Date>1453408335487</Date><Rating>5< /Rating>< Review>
The service consultant went out of her way to explain little things, which I did not get during my prior visits:
1. My car requires synthetic oil rather than the traditional. As a result, my oil change frequency is every ~ 10,000 rather than every ~5,000. I did not know that prior to this recent visit and I have visited this dealer every ~5,000 miles. Yes, I was not told until now.
2. She demonstrated to me how to reset the warning light indicator that my car needs service. Interestingly enough the warning light flashes every ~5,000 miles rather than ~10,000. She explained further that it is a kind of a reminder to check the car's oil level to make sure it does not run dry.
3. Timely notification that my car is done and ready for pick-up
4. Discussed potential issues noted by the mechanic during this visit
5. Bottom-line? The service is as good as it gets.< /Review>

This review comes late from a March purchase I made at Toyota of Lancaster.

What ended up happening is that Toyota financing ran my credit so many times causing so many inquiries to my credit, all just to come back and they tell me they are NOT able to offer me a lower interest rate than my credit union. <review>In my opinion, never buy at night without supper, insufficient lighting,  and tired!  We bought at dusk/night.  I was really hungry and if I had eaten, I would have waited to next day.  The brochures showed a solid wheel for the Toyota Camry Hybrid, which I thought was in the package we purchased, not cheap wheels with plastic covers we discovered the next day at home.  Shock.  Coupled with our really poor fuel economy driving home ~34 Miles Per Gallon, I was super frustrated.

My wife had driven to dealership to install LoJack.  When done, she drove home.  Turned out that the LoJack installation was not completed.  Had it not been for a remote LoJack install cancellation(?) call we would not have even known the install was incomplete.  In any event...

Arriving at Service, Sean greeted us.  He was very good, polite, patient.  He listened, then explained features that were unclear to me at time of purchase.  I felt that the LoJack issue was remedied justly on the part of dealership.  Upon completion of the LoJack, Sean took a few more minutes to assure that my wife and I were familiar with the car, answering our many questions.  These were more of a technical nature. He patiently listened to each question then gave clear answers.  I WAS IMPRESSED WITH SEAN.  In fact as he suggested, our road milage did improve as he predicted was common, going from a paltry 34 MPG to 49.5 MPG on the road.  WE STILL HAVE NOT SEEN 50 MPG, OR CLOSE TO IT, IN CITY, BUT HOPE TO SEE THAT SOON AS WELL.

The young salesman, Colin, walked us through our purchase also came over.  He had noticed us drive in and welcomed us. Polite, TRUTHFUL, and while new to Toyota, he made a very favorable impression upon us.  He is a keeper.

We also stopped to see Ian in finance, who also walked me through various points in the invoice that seemed like double billing to me earlier.  I knew him from earlier purchases.  He was ill the day of purchase and sounded worse on our last visit.  Despite this, he was patient, considerate, and explained each line of the contract.  I already knew him to be truthful from earlier deals settled in his office years earlier.

In terms of facility/customer care - the customer waiting area was clean, friendly, spacious.  Both shuttle drivers were terrific, prompt, courteous, very good driving skills, safe!

Finally, we are delighted to hear Wright is the new owner.  Wright Toyota in Bakersfield has a manager, Kevin J,  who remains probably the most ethical and trustworthy auto sales guy I ever met.  I realize that it will take a little time, but frankly, if Wright builds on what was first established in Lancaster and develops staff like Manager Jergens, I think Toyota of Lancaster will become one very awesome company.

We wish them the very best.

J Theisen</review><Pics>None< /Pics><Rating>4<//Rating>< GmapID>

< Review>
Ladies and Gentlemen, there is no longer the need to drive over the hill for a good deal! This dealership is under new management and you can tell from the moment you step onto the lot. I had to ditch my faulty VW Jetta and jump int another car without breaking the wallet. Not only did these guys help me get a great deal, they also managed to get me into a better car (security, safety, and features wise). I worked with Troy and he not only made the process extremely simple and easy, he was also friendly and knowledgeable on the entire Toyota lineup. Keep your taxes at home and help out the Lancaster economy by shopping local, and now you can do so without sacrificing value. A word of warning though, I came in with a pretty great credit score so I was an easy customer to deal with. Anyways big thanks to Michael for his professionalism. Even with me ranting and raving he remained calm and professional and understood my concerns. He heard me out and apologized for the inconveinence.He explained things well and did a great job. 5 star rating for Michael.< /text>
